(File) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Johannesburg - Fourteen men were arrested in Welkom on Wednesday while allegedly packing cool drinks for illegal miners, Free State police said.Spokesperson Molebogeng Lechesa said the men were caught red-handed, packing cool drinks meant for the illegal miners (zama zamas) underground."The suspects were found in a garage of a certain house in St Helena, Welkom and were immediately arrested," she said.Police confiscated bags full of cool drinks and wrapping plastics."She said the drinks had an estimated value of R250 000.The men were expected to appear in the Welkom Magistrate's Court on Thursday facing charges of conspiracy to steal gold and for attempted gold theft, she said. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.